JOHANNESBURG (miningweekly.com) &ndash; Michiel Jakobus Br&ouml;nn has resigned as COO of Coal of Africa (CoAL). This follows after the Financial Services Board recently having fined him R350 000 for insider trading. Br&ouml;nn will forfeit all share-based incentive awards and shall not be entitled to receive any bonus payments for the financial year ending June 30.